        "description": {
            "value": "<p><em>You attempt to cancel the effects of a spell using your own magic.</em></p><p><strong>Reaction</strong> - 60 ft. - 1st Level (Abjuration) - VS</p><p>You can use this reaction when within line of sight of at least one target or part of the area of effect for a spell that is about to take effect. You counter the entire spell.</p><p>The spell slot level used for Counterspell determines what it can counter.</p><ul><li><p>If the target spell is lower level than your Counterspell, including cantrips, the target spell fails and has no effect.</p></li><li><p>If the target spell is the same level as your counterspell, roll 1d20 + your intelligence modifier. If you roll at least 10 + the spell's level, the target spell fails and has no effect.</p></li><li><p>If the target spell is higher level than your Counterspell, you cannot use Counterspell.</p></li></ul><p></p><p><strong>Upcasting:</strong> See above for details.</p>",
            "chat": "<strong>Reaction</strong> - 60 ft. - 1st Level (Abjuration) - VS</p><p>You can use this reaction when within line of sight of at least one target or part of the area of effect for a spell that is about to take effect. You counter the entire spell.</p><p>The spell slot level used for Counterspell determines what it can counter.</p><ul><li><p>If the target spell is lower level than your Counterspell, including cantrips, the target spell fails and has no effect.</p></li><li><p>If the target spell is the same level as your counterspell, roll 1d20 + your intelligence modifier. If you roll at least 10 + the spell's level, the target spell fails and has no effect.</p></li><li><p>If the target spell is higher level than your Counterspell, you cannot use Counterspell.</p></li></ul><p></p><p><strong>Upcasting:</strong> See above for details.</p>"
